# ARIA Framework Rules — Windsurf IDE

This repository uses **ARIA (Atomic Responsibility Interface Architecture)**. Apply these rules to all AI completions and code generation.

> Primer: `skills/aria-primer.md` · Docs: `docs/` · Schema: `aria/schema/aria-manifest.schema.json`

---

## Pillar 1 — Layers (WHERE)

Every ARU belongs to exactly one layer. Only downward dependencies allowed — no cycles, no upward imports.

| Layer | Name      | Responsibility                       | Deps   |
|-------|-----------|--------------------------------------|--------|
| L0    | Primitive | Types, constants, pure functions     | None   |
| L1    | Atom      | Single-responsibility operations     | L0     |
| L2    | Molecule  | Composes atoms, one sub-purpose      | L0–L1  |
| L3    | Organism  | Business rules and decisions         | L0–L2  |
| L4    | System    | Orchestration only                   | L0–L3  |
| L5    | Domain    | Bounded context / integration surface| L0–L4  |

- **L0**: No side effects. No imports.
- **L3**: Business logic lives here. No direct DB/HTTP calls — use L1/L2 adapters.
- **L4**: No business logic. Only sequencing and routing.
- Same-layer coupling only through explicitly declared interfaces.

---

## Pillar 2 — ARUs (WHAT)

Every ARU: one reason to exist · one typed input · one typed output · one layer · one manifest.

**One Question Test**: "Given [input], it [single verb] and returns [output]" — no "and" in the verb phrase.

**Verb vocabulary (layer-locked):**
- L1: `validate` `transform` `compute` `generate` `encode` `decode` `hash` `compare`
- L2: `create` `build` `prepare` `assemble` `resolve`
- L3: `execute` `apply` `process` `enforce` `emit` `authorize` `persist`
- L4: `orchestrate` `coordinate` `pipeline` `route`
- L5: `expose` `integrate` `guard` `translate`

---

## Pillar 3 — Naming (Semantic Address)

```
[domain].[subdomain].[verb].[entity]   (all kebab-case)
```

Examples:
```
auth.token.validate.signature        → L1
auth.session.create.fromToken        → L2
user.registration.execute.workflow   → L3
billing.payment.orchestrate.pipeline → L4
notification.domain.expose.api       → L5
```

File naming:
```
auth.token.validate.signature.manifest.yaml
auth.token.validate.signature.ts
auth.token.validate.signature.test.ts
```

