## Pillar 5 — Semantic Graph (MAP)

`aria-build bundle ./src` assembles all manifests into a typed dependency graph. Every node is an ARU address; every edge is a pattern instance.

---

## CLI Commands

```bash
aria-build check ./src                             # validate manifests + compliance
aria-build check ./src --compliance-level 3        # enforce layer dependency rules
aria-build impact auth.identity.authenticate.user  # change impact analysis
aria-build bundle ./src                            # build semantic graph
aria-build generate ./src                          # generate TypeScript wrappers
```

---

## Do ✅ / Don't ❌

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|---------|
| Assign every ARU a layer (L0–L5) | Write code without a manifest |
| Use `domain.subdomain.verb.entity` naming | Use `utils`, `helpers`, `manager` |
| Declare every connection as a named pattern | Leave connections implicit |
| Keep L4 free of business logic | Add `if (isPremium)` in L4 Systems |
| Keep L3 free of infrastructure | Call DB directly from L3 Organisms |
| Run `aria-build check` before committing | Push without validation |
